                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "PURPOSE"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 9,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The purpose of this Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) is to:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 10,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Document  and  standardise  the  process  for  recording  consultant  to  consultant  patient referrals in Lorenzo."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 11,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Document and standardise the process for tracking and updating the patient's pathway status to ensure accurate RTT information is recorded"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 12,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Provide a baseline for future process improvements"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 13,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Assist in developing baseline for the development of training material"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 14,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Please refer to the OPD01 \u2013 Outpatients: Referral Management and Access Planning for a detailed description of end to end outpatient procedure."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 15,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Overview"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 16,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "When a consultant refers a patient to a consultant in another service within the MEHT, a new referral should be recorded in Lorenzo EPR. This new referral must be linked to the original referral as part of the patient pathway \u2013 Please see the detailed steps below."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Con2con referrals are made for the same condition, where there are new symptoms that cannot be treated in the original treatment function (service)."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "However, where the referral is raised for a new condition and a new pathway needs to start, the patient should be referred back to their GP so that a new pathway can be started via a new GP referral to the Trust. This is in line with South East Essex Consultant to consultant (C2C) Protocol agreed in 2018/19 \u2013 please see Appendix"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Furthermore, when a patient has completed their care with a consultant and is to be cared for by a CNS or a lead nurse, a referral must not be added on Lorenzo to record this care.  The nurse led care must be recorded against the initial consultant referral."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Additional guidance"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Prior to adding a new referral to a patient's record, the user must review the active referrals in the referrals tab of patients EPR in Lorenzo, to see if the patient has an active referral in the same service. If this is the case then a new referral must not be created as this will start a new pathway in Lorenzo."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Staff must escalate referrals that have incomplete details to their supervisor before this can be added to Lorenzo EPR."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Role - Administrative"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Specific Procedure- Recording a consultant to consultant referral for the same condition."
            }
        },
