        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Please note \u2013 If there is an active referral for the same service in the patients record, then the dialogue box below will appear."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Select No; the user must not create another referral if there is an open one for the same service in the patient's record as this will start another 18 week pathway in the same service and introduce a duplicate referral to the patient's record in Lorenzo."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 31,
            "data": {
                "url": "MEHTSOP009 Recording Consultant to Consultant Referrals on Lorenzo 7.0.004.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "The user must review the active/open referrals in the Referrals tab patients EPR in Lorenzo, to see if the patient has an active referral in the same service."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 33,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "If this is the case then a new referral must not be created as this will start a new pathway in Lorenzo. Staff must escalate referrals that have incomplete details to their supervisor."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 34,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "End Point:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 35,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The referral is recorded onto Lorenzo with a status of \u2018Created', for the relevant Team or Clinician. A relevant link is made to previous referrals as required. The referral is now ready to be graded. A clerk should repeat this process each day to record all referrals that have been received."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "sequence_num": 36,
            "data": {
                "num_rows": 7,
                "num_cols": 1,
                "table_items": [
                    {
                        "text": "Additional Guidance \u2013 As per the C2C Protocol agreed in 2018/19 (South East Essex CCGs)"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "The referral must be documented within the clinical records as a C2C referral"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "The referral is made by a consultant to a consultant, or equivalent senior clinician."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "The patient must be informed of the referral, and the reason for the referral, this should happen at the time the referral is made or as soon as feasible afterwards"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "The GP is advised and the reason/clinical history for the referral (within discharge documentation or clinic letter)"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Out of hours (after 5pm or at weekends and during public holidays), the most senior doctor will need to complete the C2C referral"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "If the referral is made following inpatient stay, the discharge letter should contain details and the reason that the referral was made."
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
